<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_771c6ce7-e446-4d97-bf1a-8ed0ccb3a0c5" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="TAS"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>H7P2</sptc><title id="_ba13ce24-fcdc-4c12-a097-93a3376aed66">Swimming pools</title><archive-num>2019: P2.7.2, TAS 2.1</archive-num><subclause id="_de3d9637-933e-433d-a0e6-136b3bc279ab" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_9e7d354c-b820-4ead-9cd0-567c6b79da84">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1487_0.7.0.xml#_4cbd9e00-0622-4dfd-9de4-913c80257732" id="_524a4e36-bfc2-46f8-b8af-4e13f008c201" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">swimming pool</xref> water recirculation system must incorporate safety measures to avoid entrapment of, or injury to, a person.</p></subclause><subclause id="_3395b0cb-084d-4dc5-9ffa-d5d33bb0c101" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_64863f7e-4996-45e7-a454-bbe6947eab7e">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p><xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1487_0.7.0.xml#_4cbd9e00-0622-4dfd-9de4-913c80257732" id="_d92c9cf4-a595-41af-b6ed-576895c74695" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">Swimming pools</xref> must be provided with an adequate water recirculation, disinfection and filtration system which is suitable and safe to use.</p></subclause><callout id="_05310a71-27cb-47d6-ad6e-6aaa1af6f408"><callout-type ncc-info-type="application"/><p>TAS H7P2(1) only applies to a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1487_0.7.0.xml#_4cbd9e00-0622-4dfd-9de4-913c80257732" id="_6f9ae1f7-288c-4d9f-9b5b-78143ecbd3d8" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">swimming pool</xref> with a depth of water more than 300 mm.</p></callout><callout id="_17ec79f5-4647-45a9-ace8-705a1619de63"><callout-type ncc-info-type="limitation"/><p>TAS H7P2(2) does not apply to a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1487_0.7.0.xml#_4cbd9e00-0622-4dfd-9de4-913c80257732" id="_3627b274-b22e-44fe-9bdb-a1425dfe22fd" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">swimming pool</xref> associated with a Class 1 building if the depth of water is less than 300 mm and the volume of the pool does not exceed 15 m<sup id="_6a601849-069f-4ca2-9399-90db77d125c2">3</sup>.</p></callout></clause>